---
import '../styles/global.css';
import '../styles/terminal.css';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>about.txt - prajan-karthik</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="terminal-window">
        <div class="panel-header">
          <a href="/">← prajan-karthik@prajan-83dx</a> / about.txt
        </div>

        <div class="terminal-prompt">$ cat about.txt</div>
        <div class="terminal-output">
          <div class="panel">
            <div class="panel-header">Background</div>
            <div class="panel-content">
              <p>I'm a Computer Science undergraduate with a passion for building scalable systems and solving complex problems. My journey in tech started with curiosity about how things work, which led me to explore everything from low-level systems to high-level web applications.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="panel">
            <div class="panel-header">Focus Areas</div>
            <div class="panel-content">
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Full-stack Development:</strong> Building end-to-end applications with modern frameworks</li>
                <li><strong>Distributed Systems:</strong> Designing scalable architectures and concurrent systems</li>
                <li><strong>Data Engineering:</strong> Web scraping, data pipelines, and ML integration</li>
                <li><strong>Linux & Open Source:</strong> Contributing to the ecosystem and understanding system internals</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="panel">
            <div class="panel-header">Experience</div>
            <div class="panel-content">
              <p><strong>Intel IoT Club:</strong> Working on IoT projects and embedded systems</p>
              <p><strong>Hackathons:</strong> Participating in and winning hackathons like IndiaRuns</p>
              <p><strong>Open Source:</strong> Contributing to various projects and building tools for the community</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="panel">
            <div class="panel-header">Philosophy</div>
            <div class="panel-content">
              <p>I believe in building systems that are not only functional but also maintainable, scalable, and well-documented. I enjoy diving deep into problems to understand their root causes and architect solutions that stand the test of time.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="panel">
            <div class="panel-header">When I'm not coding</div>
            <div class="panel-content">
              <p>Exploring Linux distributions, optimizing my workflow, reading about system design, and occasionally gaming.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="terminal-prompt">$ cd /</div>
        <div class="terminal-output">
          <a href="/">Return to home →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1rem;
  }

  .panel-content ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding-left: 0;
  }

  .panel-content li {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .panel-content li::before {
    content: "•";
    color: var(--accent);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
  }

  .panel-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
</style>
